1
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:14,250
(This program is intended for mature audiences.
It may feature explicit content, violence, and strong language)

2
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:19,700
(All characters, places, and events
in this series are entirely fictitious)

3
00:00:20,722 --> 00:00:22,977
Sorry to bother you.

4
00:00:23,719 --> 00:00:24,985
If something's wrong, you can tell me.

5
00:00:26,412 --> 00:00:27,634
We're in the same boat now.

6
00:00:29,875 --> 00:00:31,316
In that case...

7
00:00:32,771 --> 00:00:34,794
Could you take me and Singto in?

8
00:00:37,355 --> 00:00:38,766
I have nowhere else to go.

9
00:00:40,251 --> 00:00:41,022
Of course.

10
00:00:44,121 --> 00:00:45,679
I'll take care of you and Singto.

11
00:00:50,292 --> 00:00:55,164
=Love of Silom=

12
00:01:06,939 --> 00:01:07,667
Come in first.

13
00:01:18,930 --> 00:01:20,618
Do you live here alone?

14
00:01:21,142 --> 00:01:22,233
Hm. Yeah.

15
00:01:22,481 --> 00:01:24,212
Sorry, it's a little messy.

16
00:01:30,703 --> 00:01:32,638
Have a seat. Want something to drink?

17
00:01:32,638 --> 00:01:34,661
Tea, coffee, or water?

18
00:01:36,873 --> 00:01:38,008
Anything's fine.

19
00:01:52,458 --> 00:01:53,680
Make yourself at home.

20
00:01:53,971 --> 00:01:55,063
Think of it as your own home.

21
00:02:01,451 --> 00:02:02,324
Water.

22
00:02:03,052 --> 00:02:04,536
Singto, have some water first.

23
00:02:05,919 --> 00:02:07,258
You can take a shower first.

24
00:02:07,258 --> 00:02:08,655
I'll watch Singto for you.

25
00:02:09,906 --> 00:02:11,230
- Uh...
- Oh.

26
00:02:11,434 --> 00:02:13,151
You can borrow my clothes for now.
It's fine.

27
00:02:13,777 --> 00:02:14,868
Just relax.

28
00:02:16,876 --> 00:02:17,851
Thank you.

29
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:20,820
Come on, let's sit on the couch.

30
00:02:21,431 --> 00:02:22,843
- Oof.
- There we go.

31
00:02:23,105 --> 00:02:24,589
- Stay with him for now, okay?
- Hmm.

32
00:02:24,822 --> 00:02:25,564
Oof.

33
00:02:26,554 --> 00:02:27,150
There we go.

34
00:02:28,227 --> 00:02:28,926
Come on.

35
00:02:29,786 --> 00:02:30,394
Come here.

36
00:02:31,268 --> 00:02:32,811
Sit down and rest for a bit.

37
00:02:33,626 --> 00:02:34,311
Okay.

38
00:02:38,938 --> 00:02:39,880
Oops.

39
00:02:42,721 --> 00:02:43,361
Chicken.

40
00:02:43,958 --> 00:02:45,064
Um

41
00:02:45,297 --> 00:02:46,854
Why do you eat this again?

42
00:02:47,101 --> 00:02:49,284
- Going home.
- Going home?

43
00:03:00,186 --> 00:03:00,986
Alas.

44
00:03:10,166 --> 00:03:11,316
Come and color with us.

45
00:03:15,667 --> 00:03:16,889
I'd rather not.

46
00:03:17,937 --> 00:03:18,621
Why not?

47
00:03:19,858 --> 00:03:22,768
Afraid it won't turn out well?
No need to be shy.

48
00:03:23,066 --> 00:03:23,907
Tsk.

49
00:03:25,359 --> 00:03:27,570
Could anything be more embarrassing
than that sheet of paper?

50
00:03:31,354 --> 00:03:33,857
That's just how an artist's work is.

51
00:03:37,699 --> 00:03:38,412
Right?

52
00:03:42,138 --> 00:03:42,826
Come on.

53
00:03:43,258 --> 00:03:44,596
So, what are you doing?

54
00:03:44,931 --> 00:03:45,659
Oof.

55
00:03:48,186 --> 00:03:49,152
Ow.

56
00:03:49,544 --> 00:03:50,388
Want to draw?

57
00:03:53,691 --> 00:03:56,427
- Draw.
- Go on, draw something.

58
00:03:58,465 --> 00:03:59,585
You're amazing.

59
00:04:00,618 --> 00:04:03,107
Being the head of the family
at such a young age.

60
00:04:08,549 --> 00:04:09,786
I'm not that amazing.

61
00:04:12,929 --> 00:04:15,156
Right now, I feel like...

62
00:04:17,353 --> 00:04:22,112
I'm stuck running on a hamster wheel.

63
00:04:23,945 --> 00:04:27,714
No matter how exhausted I get,
I can't stop.

64
00:04:31,862 --> 00:04:35,514
I keep struggling with
the same problems, over and over.

65
00:05:00,218 --> 00:05:01,370
Hold this.

66
00:05:02,406 --> 00:05:03,236
Excuse me a sec.

67
00:05:06,970 --> 00:05:07,836
Hold this.

68
00:05:11,065 --> 00:05:11,793
Alright.

69
00:05:27,232 --> 00:05:27,931
Here.

70
00:05:29,401 --> 00:05:30,405
Want some tea?

71
00:05:31,190 --> 00:05:32,718
They say it helps with stress.

72
00:05:33,984 --> 00:05:35,381
I'm not stressed.

73
00:05:36,837 --> 00:05:39,674
With your brows all knitted up
like that, what else would you call it?

74
00:05:45,248 --> 00:05:48,202
Wow, that's actually really good.

75
00:05:49,264 --> 00:05:50,399
You've clearly got talent.

76
00:05:52,189 --> 00:05:53,572
I'm not trying to show off.

77
00:05:54,881 --> 00:05:57,442
But I'm an architecture student.

78
00:05:59,713 --> 00:06:01,095
Now that sounds like showing off.

79
00:06:10,292 --> 00:06:12,358
Hey, don't you need to get back to work?

80
00:06:12,460 --> 00:06:14,148
I can stay here with Singto.

81
00:06:14,556 --> 00:06:16,200
Okay, then...

82
00:06:17,975 --> 00:06:20,769
Wayu, I'll hurry back
before you have to leave for work.

83
00:06:22,472 --> 00:06:23,680
You're already calling me 'Wayu'?

84
00:06:26,285 --> 00:06:27,915
And you still call me 'Krit.'

85
00:06:30,912 --> 00:06:31,902
I'll be back soon.

86
00:06:32,586 --> 00:06:35,511
Hey, no need to rush, Krit.

87
00:06:35,627 --> 00:06:37,824
It's a major Buddhist holiday today,
so the club is closed.

88
00:06:38,945 --> 00:06:39,935
Oh, really?

89
00:06:40,182 --> 00:06:40,969
Then...

90
00:06:42,657 --> 00:06:44,585
- You can stay here by yourself, right?
- Of course.

91
00:06:44,926 --> 00:06:47,764
I won't rob your room or anything.
You can trust me.

92
00:06:49,190 --> 00:06:50,470
Let me know if you need anything.

93
00:06:50,616 --> 00:06:53,366
Well, if you want anything,
just help yourself.

94
00:06:54,414 --> 00:06:57,412
You can sleep in my bedroom tonight.

95
00:06:57,630 --> 00:06:58,925
I'll sleep on the couch.

96
00:06:59,216 --> 00:07:00,948
Okay. You should get going.

97
00:07:00,948 --> 00:07:03,174
Your phone's been ringing off the hook.

98
00:08:12,413 --> 00:08:16,066
(New post: I don't want to stop
on Saturdays or Sundays.)

99
00:08:16,779 --> 00:08:21,522
(Or even on public holidays.
I only want to stop when I'm with you.)

100
00:08:31,418 --> 00:08:34,212
(Thai police are dedicated
to public safety)

101
00:08:40,178 --> 00:08:42,841
It was just a regular party
my client attended.

102
00:08:42,972 --> 00:08:44,559
Actually, you...

103
00:08:44,559 --> 00:08:47,294
you don't even have grounds
to detain Mr. Supanat.

104
00:08:50,170 --> 00:08:50,888
There.

105
00:08:53,435 --> 00:08:55,691
(The printed chat log shown to Nut)

106
00:08:55,764 --> 00:08:57,059
This is the chat evidence.

107
00:08:57,175 --> 00:09:00,028
It shows Mr. Supanat
luring the victims to the party.

108
00:09:08,031 --> 00:09:09,210
And it seems...

109
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:12,266
it wasn't just an ordinary party.

110
00:09:12,586 --> 00:09:13,401
Whoa.

111
00:09:15,730 --> 00:09:16,836
(Need 20 NV N/UP girls. Good-looking.)

112
00:09:16,836 --> 00:09:17,913
(Party till morning, no complaints.
Sign up if interested.)

113
00:09:17,913 --> 00:09:19,105
(- Interested+1)
(- I'm interested.)

114
00:09:19,513 --> 00:09:20,415
Officer.

115
00:09:21,274 --> 00:09:23,820
Can these chat evidence be fabricated?

116
00:09:24,038 --> 00:09:26,556
You're arresting me just for this?

117
00:09:27,662 --> 00:09:28,244
Hmph.

118
00:09:30,441 --> 00:09:31,314
And what about this?

119
00:09:33,308 --> 00:09:34,938
I found it right on your phone.

120
00:09:35,855 --> 00:09:38,474
(Chainphop Udomdirek/Supanut Tosakarn)

121
00:09:41,035 --> 00:09:42,796
Why did Mr. Chain transfer money to you?

122
00:09:44,775 --> 00:09:46,449
And such a large amount of money?

123
00:09:47,002 --> 00:09:49,665
Transferring almost every month,
what is it for?

124
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,542
Or are you buying something?

125
00:09:57,174 --> 00:09:59,385
And what about these photos
of people in your house?

126
00:10:01,015 --> 00:10:02,718
Many people have gone missing.

127
00:10:02,718 --> 00:10:04,784
Many are victims
in human trafficking cases.

128
00:10:05,788 --> 00:10:07,695
Did you sell these people to Mr. Chain?

129
00:10:08,073 --> 00:10:10,241
Officer, have you forgotten that

130
00:10:10,270 --> 00:10:11,420
I'm a producer?

131
00:10:11,420 --> 00:10:13,938
These influencers want work,

132
00:10:13,938 --> 00:10:15,116
so they have to come to me.

133
00:10:15,116 --> 00:10:16,601
Everyone wants money, right?

134
00:10:16,746 --> 00:10:18,245
I haven't told you yet

135
00:10:19,031 --> 00:10:21,214
that these people are "influencers."

136
00:10:22,712 --> 00:10:26,234
There've been tons of news reports.
Do you even pay attention?

137
00:10:26,467 --> 00:10:28,897
What is all this about?

138
00:10:28,897 --> 00:10:30,702
I told you, I don't know
anything about it.

139
00:10:31,691 --> 00:10:34,412
Officer, didn't you request
a search warrant on drug-related charges?

140
00:10:34,572 --> 00:10:36,959
And did you find any drugs
at Mr. Supanat's house?

141
00:10:38,705 --> 00:10:39,491
No, we didn't.

142
00:10:40,772 --> 00:10:42,692
His urine test results are normal.

143
00:10:42,692 --> 00:10:45,137
Then do you still intend
to question Mr. Supanat

144
00:10:45,137 --> 00:10:46,825
about drugs, or not?

145
00:10:47,626 --> 00:10:48,732
If not,

146
00:10:49,721 --> 00:10:51,991
I request permission
to take Mr. Supanut back now.

147
00:10:53,825 --> 00:10:54,582
Let's go.

148
00:10:55,789 --> 00:10:57,259
I'm clean.

149
00:10:59,442 --> 00:11:00,621
It's darn freezing.

150
00:11:02,032 --> 00:11:03,560
They wouldn't even let me get dressed.

151
00:11:17,414 --> 00:11:18,389
I'm back.

152
00:11:31,413 --> 00:11:34,542
Mm. You're still awake?

153
00:12:06,993 --> 00:12:08,113
Come, Singto.

154
00:12:08,783 --> 00:12:11,617
Want to sit on my lap and watch?
Come here.

155
00:12:13,265 --> 00:12:15,186
Scoot over a little.

156
00:12:18,096 --> 00:12:18,998
Can you see?

157
00:13:07,166 --> 00:13:09,480
(Pete)

158
00:13:16,450 --> 00:13:17,323
Is it good?

159
00:13:41,261 --> 00:13:42,702
You're up. Come eat with us.

160
00:13:42,702 --> 00:13:44,506
Mom, come eat.

161
00:13:44,506 --> 00:13:45,338
Hehe.

162
00:13:46,042 --> 00:13:50,429
Oh.

163
00:13:50,429 --> 00:13:51,375
Oh.

164
00:13:53,194 --> 00:13:55,522
What are you cooking? Smells nice.

165
00:13:57,152 --> 00:13:59,931
Singto, oh.

166
00:14:01,896 --> 00:14:04,414
So is this a sleep-with-me,
free-breakfast deal?

167
00:14:04,908 --> 00:14:06,538
No, you're sleeping with Singto.

168
00:14:06,713 --> 00:14:08,008
Not sleeping with me at all.

169
00:14:10,118 --> 00:14:12,388
Oh, so that means...

170
00:14:13,130 --> 00:14:15,124
if I slept with you,

171
00:14:15,546 --> 00:14:18,078
breakfast wouldn't be free then.

172
00:14:19,984 --> 00:14:21,410
You'd probably get more than breakfast.

173
00:14:23,389 --> 00:14:24,321
Um...

174
00:14:27,217 --> 00:14:29,472
When did you get back last night?

175
00:14:29,472 --> 00:14:30,607
I had no idea.

176
00:14:37,127 --> 00:14:40,764
Here, you've got something
on your lips. There.

177
00:14:47,691 --> 00:14:48,652
Mm, Krit.

178
00:14:49,540 --> 00:14:51,359
Have you questioned Nut yet?

179
00:14:51,359 --> 00:14:52,523
How did it go?

180
00:14:54,022 --> 00:14:55,084
He still won't admit it.

181
00:14:55,797 --> 00:14:57,543
And they didn't find any drugs
in the house, either.

182
00:14:57,936 --> 00:15:00,657
We probably need to find evidence
and catch him red-handed.

183
00:15:02,593 --> 00:15:05,765
In that case,
you can count on a spy like me.

184
00:15:07,730 --> 00:15:08,603
Woo.

185
00:15:10,902 --> 00:15:12,765
Looks like we'll have to
count on you, Mr. Spy.

186
00:15:13,783 --> 00:15:14,613
Thank you.

187
00:15:20,143 --> 00:15:21,554
- Want some?
- Are you full yet?

188
00:15:21,554 --> 00:15:23,169
Want some more? Want some?

189
00:15:24,232 --> 00:15:25,294
You're not eating?

190
00:15:25,512 --> 00:15:27,491
Dip it in the sauce first.
Want to try it with sauce?

191
00:15:34,113 --> 00:15:36,863
Let's go.

192
00:15:38,755 --> 00:15:39,759
Be careful.

193
00:15:41,549 --> 00:15:43,557
Watch your step. Uh-huh.

194
00:15:44,008 --> 00:15:46,293
Hello, Singto.

195
00:15:46,526 --> 00:15:48,025
- Hello.
- Hello.

196
00:15:48,025 --> 00:15:49,014
Be good and study hard, okay?

197
00:15:49,785 --> 00:15:52,754
Singto, Daddy will come
pick you up this evening.

198
00:15:53,540 --> 00:15:55,926
Come on, I'll take you to your friends.

199
00:15:56,130 --> 00:15:58,051
Then I'll leave Singto in your care.

200
00:15:58,051 --> 00:15:59,477
Please call me if anything comes up.

201
00:15:59,477 --> 00:16:00,656
With pleasure.

202
00:16:01,267 --> 00:16:03,260
Both dads are still young.

203
00:16:03,377 --> 00:16:04,847
- Well...
- Thank you.

204
00:16:05,763 --> 00:16:06,462
Let's go.

205
00:16:09,867 --> 00:16:11,424
Hurry up. Let's go play.

206
00:16:12,268 --> 00:16:12,865
Hup.

207
00:16:13,592 --> 00:16:14,204
Hey.

208
00:16:16,241 --> 00:16:18,016
Why didn't you tell the teacher
earlier that we...

209
00:16:18,016 --> 00:16:21,218
Well, the teacher already
has a ton to do.

210
00:16:21,334 --> 00:16:22,658
It would've taken forever to explain.

211
00:16:23,459 --> 00:16:24,972
Or were you bothered by it?

212
00:16:25,933 --> 00:16:28,115
No, not really.

213
00:16:28,887 --> 00:16:29,891
Then that's that.

214
00:16:30,589 --> 00:16:31,477
Let's split up.

215
00:16:33,398 --> 00:16:34,940
Thank you for dropping me off.

216
00:16:36,046 --> 00:16:36,934
I should get going.

217
00:16:38,768 --> 00:16:39,510
Wait.

218
00:16:43,861 --> 00:16:44,690
Sorry.

219
00:16:47,790 --> 00:16:49,507
Are you going anywhere else?

220
00:16:49,507 --> 00:16:50,497
I can drive you.

221
00:16:51,471 --> 00:16:53,392
Or you can rest at my condo first.

222
00:16:53,829 --> 00:16:55,750
You don't start work
until this evening, right?

223
00:17:04,393 --> 00:17:07,653
(Dialing number,
not received — Mom (20))

224
00:17:16,254 --> 00:17:18,189
Then could you take me home?

225
00:17:23,486 --> 00:17:24,417
My son...

226
00:17:26,076 --> 00:17:27,502
Why didn't you answer?

227
00:17:33,498 --> 00:17:34,342
Yu.

228
00:17:36,321 --> 00:17:39,464
Where have you been?
I've been worried sick.

229
00:17:39,639 --> 00:17:40,381
Hm?

230
00:17:40,381 --> 00:17:42,870
Are you worried about me
or the money, Mom?

231
00:17:44,776 --> 00:17:46,260
Are you still mad at me?

232
00:17:46,755 --> 00:17:48,545
I already kicked him out.

233
00:17:49,811 --> 00:17:53,187
At first, when we started dating,
he was sweet to me.

234
00:17:53,885 --> 00:17:56,781
But once I ran out of money,
he stopped caring about me.

235
00:17:59,677 --> 00:18:00,565
Mom...

236
00:18:01,365 --> 00:18:04,639
If you want a boyfriend or whatever,
I've never tried to stop you.

237
00:18:04,989 --> 00:18:08,176
I want you to be happy too,
and to have someone by your side.

238
00:18:08,379 --> 00:18:10,708
But please, Mom... can you choose
more wisely next time?

239
00:18:10,897 --> 00:18:13,356
Choose someone
you don't have to support.

240
00:18:13,589 --> 00:18:17,431
I'm already barely keeping up
with your debts as it is.

241
00:18:18,260 --> 00:18:19,686
I'm sorry.

242
00:18:20,356 --> 00:18:21,011
Okay?

243
00:18:21,564 --> 00:18:23,179
I'm sorry.

244
00:18:26,191 --> 00:18:27,661
Okay?

245
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:39,433
Alright.

246
00:18:49,664 --> 00:18:50,668
Is he your boyfriend?

247
00:18:51,366 --> 00:18:53,011
I've seen him drop you off
a bunch of times.

248
00:18:56,197 --> 00:18:56,925
Yes.

249
00:18:57,827 --> 00:19:00,141
I know a little about the problems
Wayu has at home.

250
00:19:00,854 --> 00:19:02,571
But I want you
to understand this, ma'am.

251
00:19:03,226 --> 00:19:04,783
Everything Wayu does,

252
00:19:04,943 --> 00:19:07,112
he does it for you and Singto.

253
00:19:11,856 --> 00:19:12,801
Listen, mom.

254
00:19:13,194 --> 00:19:17,400
He's a cop. If you start gambling again,
you'll get arrested for sure.

255
00:19:22,217 --> 00:19:26,844
That's good. If my future son-in-law
is a cop, he can help me find a way out.

256
00:19:26,844 --> 00:19:28,663
Oh, mom.

257
00:19:31,283 --> 00:19:33,664
Alright, I'll go inside first
so you two can talk.

258
00:19:33,664 --> 00:19:34,880
Okay?

259
00:19:36,442 --> 00:19:37,248
Hehe.

260
00:19:43,506 --> 00:19:44,801
Your mom's really sweet.

261
00:19:45,369 --> 00:19:46,795
Do you want to take her in?

262
00:19:46,795 --> 00:19:48,832
I'll give you two sacks of rice for free.

263
00:19:55,759 --> 00:19:58,684
Thank you for what you said back there.

264
00:20:01,740 --> 00:20:03,661
Just think of it as me doing my duty.

265
00:20:03,661 --> 00:20:05,538
Call it the "Live with a Cop" program.

266
00:20:05,727 --> 00:20:06,426
Hey.

267
00:20:06,833 --> 00:20:09,074
Isn't it supposed to be
"Leave Your House with a Cop"?

268
00:20:15,841 --> 00:20:16,612
Hey.

269
00:20:18,271 --> 00:20:20,090
About what you told my mom...

270
00:20:20,963 --> 00:20:22,375
are you sure that was okay?

271
