00:35:40,984 --> 00:35:43,133
- Yes.
- Then I'm leaving him with you.

543
00:35:53,835 --> 00:35:54,904
Mm.

544
00:36:04,055 --> 00:36:04,772
Cheers.

545
00:36:17,706 --> 00:36:18,681
Do you have a partner?

546
00:36:19,844 --> 00:36:22,828
You know people in this line of work
can't have partner, right?

547
00:36:23,215 --> 00:36:23,861
Oh.

548
00:36:24,883 --> 00:36:25,999
I kind of know.

549
00:36:25,999 --> 00:36:27,785
But honestly, it depends
on the person, Nut.

550
00:36:28,243 --> 00:36:30,264
As for me, I'm single.

551
00:36:33,130 --> 00:36:34,704
Are you just saying that
to butter me up?

552
00:36:34,869 --> 00:36:36,184
No, not at all.

553
00:36:36,537 --> 00:36:37,712
I'm truly single.

554
00:36:38,229 --> 00:36:39,392
And I'm...

555
00:36:40,190 --> 00:36:41,353
still a virgin too.

556
00:36:43,245 --> 00:36:44,320
Now that's rare.

557
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:45,139
Heh.

558
00:36:52,954 --> 00:36:53,530
Hm.

559
00:37:00,889 --> 00:37:01,571
Oh.

560
00:37:03,192 --> 00:37:03,955
Mm.

561
00:37:05,858 --> 00:37:06,634
Huh.

562
00:37:07,444 --> 00:37:09,347
This one packs a punch.

563
00:37:10,052 --> 00:37:10,675
Really?

564
00:37:11,897 --> 00:37:13,048
Want to change that?

565
00:37:13,870 --> 00:37:15,033
No, it's fine.

566
00:37:16,032 --> 00:37:17,042
I can drink.

567
00:37:56,760 --> 00:37:58,181
I'll take care of the rest myself.

568
00:37:59,438 --> 00:38:00,237
Thanks, man.

569
00:38:11,973 --> 00:38:13,418
Let me see.

570
00:38:18,457 --> 00:38:19,785
Boss, the cops are here.

571
00:38:23,591 --> 00:38:25,788
- Stay here. Don't go up.
- This way, please.

572
00:38:37,288 --> 00:38:39,109
(Nut)

573
00:38:40,131 --> 00:38:45,782
(Good-looking, 23, still a virgin.
This one's worth a high price.)

574
00:38:48,977 --> 00:38:50,269
Darn it, the cops are here.

575
00:38:53,323 --> 00:38:54,040
Hey!

576
00:38:54,721 --> 00:38:57,564
- Foei, hey!
- What happened?

577
00:39:00,501 --> 00:39:02,275
Darn it, I'm asking what's happened.

578
00:39:03,567 --> 00:39:04,660
The cops are here.

579
00:39:05,083 --> 00:39:06,739
But I've already taken care of it.

580
00:39:09,723 --> 00:39:12,084
- Hey, do something!
- Darn it.

581
00:39:38,554 --> 00:39:39,378
Yikes!

582
00:40:14,157 --> 00:40:14,897
Wayu!

583
00:40:15,438 --> 00:40:16,166
Wayu!

584
00:40:16,847 --> 00:40:17,623
Wayu!

585
00:40:24,554 --> 00:40:26,774
Someone's hurt inside. Send help!

586
00:40:52,947 --> 00:40:55,074
(Thai police are dedicated
to public safety)

587
00:40:59,514 --> 00:41:02,709
Ow.

588
00:41:04,412 --> 00:41:05,282
Ow.

589
00:41:05,987 --> 00:41:07,091
Why'd you get up so fast?

590
00:41:08,724 --> 00:41:09,793
You're going to get dizzy.

591
00:41:10,709 --> 00:41:11,520
Krit.

592
00:41:13,575 --> 00:41:14,997
Ow, hey.

593
00:41:16,735 --> 00:41:18,157
How did I end up here?

594
00:41:19,813 --> 00:41:21,434
Did I get hit on the head again?

595
00:41:22,233 --> 00:41:23,384
Ah.

596
00:41:24,336 --> 00:41:25,476
You were drugged.

597
00:41:26,662 --> 00:41:27,919
Good thing I got there in time.

598
00:41:28,318 --> 00:41:29,846
Otherwise, you'd be across
the border by now.

599
00:41:30,879 --> 00:41:31,490
Hey.

600
00:41:32,160 --> 00:41:33,863
Being brave is one thing,

601
00:41:34,451 --> 00:41:36,412
but what's more important
is following orders.

602
00:41:36,964 --> 00:41:38,398
Otherwise, the whole plan
could fall apart.

603
00:41:38,738 --> 00:41:42,192
You got lucky and made it out today.
What if you aren't so lucky next time?

604
00:41:42,791 --> 00:41:44,354
You didn't answer my call.

605
00:41:46,104 --> 00:41:47,431
You didn't reply to my messages, either.

606
00:41:48,630 --> 00:41:52,541
So I thought if I went,
I might find something more.

607
00:41:54,245 --> 00:41:56,077
That's why I decided to go.

608
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:59,050
Let this be a lesson, then.

609
00:41:59,290 --> 00:41:59,881
Ow.

610
00:42:00,483 --> 00:42:01,669
But don't do that again.

611
00:42:02,891 --> 00:42:04,277
If I don't answer the phone,

612
00:42:04,794 --> 00:42:06,744
don't go solo, got it?

613
00:42:08,659 --> 00:42:09,540
Got it?

614
00:42:10,515 --> 00:42:11,185
Yes.

615
00:42:13,511 --> 00:42:14,509
I'm sorry.

616
00:42:19,866 --> 00:42:20,723
Ow.

617
00:42:28,888 --> 00:42:29,828
Thank you.

618
00:42:41,458 --> 00:42:42,280
Hello, Captain.

619
00:42:43,878 --> 00:42:44,782
Captain.

620
00:42:46,168 --> 00:42:46,897
What is it?

621
00:42:47,284 --> 00:42:50,151
Well, Mr. Supanat has been released.

622
00:42:51,713 --> 00:42:52,524
Who released him?

623
00:42:52,888 --> 00:42:54,039
Inspector Athip.

624
00:42:54,415 --> 00:42:58,503
Someone confessed to hiring
Mr. Supanat to organize the party.

625
00:42:58,503 --> 00:43:02,215
And there's evidence that all the drugs
belonged to the person who confessed.

626
00:43:02,697 --> 00:43:05,246
That weakened the case
against Mr. Supanat,

627
00:43:05,246 --> 00:43:06,573
so we had to let him go.

628
00:43:07,196 --> 00:43:08,218
I knew he'd slip through.

629
00:43:10,767 --> 00:43:12,976
Have someone keep an eye on Por for now.

630
00:43:13,434 --> 00:43:14,962
You mean Por Wichai?

631
00:43:14,962 --> 00:43:16,441
Why do we need to watch him?

632
00:43:16,606 --> 00:43:17,816
I think Por

633
00:43:18,309 --> 00:43:21,023
might be backing both Mr. Supanat
and Mr. Chainphop.

634
00:43:22,444 --> 00:43:23,090
Yes, sir.

635
00:43:28,870 --> 00:43:30,291
Yeah, Tai.

636
00:43:30,444 --> 00:43:32,723
I'm really fine now,
I can go back to work.

637
00:43:32,723 --> 00:43:33,816
You should rest.

638
00:43:33,816 --> 00:43:35,378
I've already taken leave for you
from Madam Foei.

639
00:43:35,496 --> 00:43:37,504
I said you had food poisoning.

640
00:43:38,409 --> 00:43:39,666
Alright, okay.

641
00:43:40,700 --> 00:43:43,860
Thanks for calling the Captain for me.

642
00:43:43,860 --> 00:43:47,572
Otherwise, I probably would've been
shipped off to the border by now.

643
00:43:47,842 --> 00:43:50,908
Yeah, I know you want
to help with this case.

644
00:43:50,990 --> 00:43:52,776
But you've got to
look after yourself too.

645
00:43:52,823 --> 00:43:55,407
Oh Tai, can you stop nagging me already?

646
00:43:55,407 --> 00:43:58,039
The Captain chewed me out so much.
I didn't even get a chance to feel guilty.

647
00:43:58,039 --> 00:43:59,495
Well, you had it coming.

648
00:43:59,895 --> 00:44:01,633
Alright, that's enough.
I'm getting back to my workout.

649
00:44:01,633 --> 00:44:03,560
Hey Tai, wait a sec.

650
00:44:06,203 --> 00:44:07,824
Hup, hup.

651
00:44:10,432 --> 00:44:11,231
Tai.

652
00:44:12,829 --> 00:44:14,720
Ugh, what is it with you?

653
00:44:17,046 --> 00:44:17,798
Alas.

654
00:44:29,592 --> 00:44:36,711
(To Krit: Wayu: how are you? I'm off today,
so let me know if I can help.)

655
00:44:41,704 --> 00:44:45,862
(Deleting data)

656
00:44:48,634 --> 00:44:49,563
Ah.

657
00:45:04,341 --> 00:45:07,325
(Krit: Can we meet this evening?
I'd like to talk about the case.)

658
00:45:10,262 --> 00:45:13,163
(Sure, let's meet this evening.)

659
00:45:20,341 --> 00:45:21,104
Well,

660
00:45:21,798 --> 00:45:25,486
Nut's lawyer is from the same firm
as Por's lawyer.

661
00:45:26,238 --> 00:45:28,317
And most of the party venues

662
00:45:29,140 --> 00:45:32,159
are in Por's turf, so no one interferes.

663
00:45:34,485 --> 00:45:37,985
Por might be backing Nut and Chain.

664
00:45:38,467 --> 00:45:39,783
But we don't have any evidence yet.

665
00:45:42,097 --> 00:45:42,861
Then...

666
00:45:43,577 --> 00:45:44,869
try kissing him.

667
00:45:44,869 --> 00:45:47,513
If he's really straight,
he'll definitely turn you down.

668
00:45:47,513 --> 00:45:49,087
But if he kisses you back,

669
00:45:49,357 --> 00:45:51,554
you can go ahead
and start planning the wedding, buddy.

670
00:45:51,554 --> 00:45:53,057
So, what do you want me to do?

671
00:45:57,263 --> 00:45:59,542
Uh... nothing.

672
00:45:59,789 --> 00:46:00,987
Sorry, it's just...

673
00:46:01,375 --> 00:46:03,184
the voice in my head
got a little too loud.

674
00:46:03,982 --> 00:46:05,110
You can keep going, Krit.

675
00:46:06,120 --> 00:46:08,235
Well, after this,

676
00:46:08,646 --> 00:46:11,689
we'll have to keep an eye
on Por, Nut, and Chain.

677
00:46:14,167 --> 00:46:17,363
But Por seems like a man of the people.

678
00:46:17,938 --> 00:46:19,595
He donates a lot to various causes,

679
00:46:19,595 --> 00:46:21,768
and he helps people in need too.

680
00:46:23,048 --> 00:46:26,103
Could he really be involved
in human trafficking?

681
00:46:28,065 --> 00:46:29,016
You never know.

682
00:46:29,674 --> 00:46:33,339
What you see and what really is
might be two different things.

683
00:46:40,399 --> 00:46:42,208
Uh, well,

684
00:46:42,349 --> 00:46:44,558
sorry to interrupt.

685
00:46:44,957 --> 00:46:45,733
Krit,

686
00:46:46,954 --> 00:46:48,200
can you close the shop for me?

687
00:46:48,200 --> 00:46:50,103
I need to head home.
My mom's calling me back.

688
00:46:50,244 --> 00:46:52,299
Oh, your mom's back from England?

689
00:46:58,302 --> 00:47:01,169
You really do keep tabs
on my mom's life, huh?

690
00:47:02,061 --> 00:47:03,824
Anyway, I need to rush back.

691
00:47:04,070 --> 00:47:06,725
- Close up for me. Bye.
- Sure.

692
00:47:08,487 --> 00:47:10,050
Make yourself at home.

693
00:47:10,285 --> 00:47:12,705
Feel free to do whatever you want.

694
00:47:13,985 --> 00:47:14,901
Thank you.

695
00:47:21,657 --> 00:47:23,255
How could you think
I'd be her boyfriend?

696
00:47:23,994 --> 00:47:25,345
I can't even picture it.

697
00:47:25,721 --> 00:47:26,672
Why?

698
00:47:27,107 --> 00:47:28,646
Rose is really nice.

699
00:47:28,752 --> 00:47:32,464
I think you're lucky
to have her as a friend.

700
00:47:36,575 --> 00:47:37,292
That's true.

701
00:48:09,033 --> 00:48:11,477
It's really hot here.

702
00:48:15,483 --> 00:48:16,798
I'll sit here instead.

703
00:48:22,214 --> 00:48:23,412
The air conditioning is cooler here.

704
00:48:38,143 --> 00:48:39,729
Are you wearing perfume today?

705
00:48:40,528 --> 00:48:42,102
You don't usually wear any.

706
00:48:45,474 --> 00:48:46,543
You're observant.

707
00:48:52,358 --> 00:48:54,049
Hey, the power's out.

708
00:48:54,319 --> 00:48:55,929
The power's out.

709
00:48:55,929 --> 00:48:57,738
- Krit, the power's out.
- Uh-huh.

710
00:48:57,738 --> 00:48:59,782
The power's out. I'm scared, Krit.

711
00:49:00,170 --> 00:49:02,002
It's so dark, Krit.

712
00:49:04,939 --> 00:49:07,195
- It's dark.
- If you're forcing it, don't.

713
00:49:08,017 --> 00:49:09,215
I know you're not really scared.

714
00:49:15,394 --> 00:49:18,519
Oops, I got caught.

715
00:49:31,888 --> 00:49:33,603
If you're really that good at guessing,

716
00:49:35,330 --> 00:49:37,222
then try guessing this.

717
00:49:39,065 --> 00:49:40,217
What am I thinking right now?

718
00:50:00,680 --> 00:50:05,133
♪Awakened from the trance of emptiness♪

719
00:50:05,285 --> 00:50:09,702
♪There's no such thing
as loneliness anymore♪

720
00:50:09,702 --> 00:50:14,542
♪Since you came and changed the story♪

721
00:50:14,965 --> 00:50:18,384
♪This heart knows only longing for you♪

722
00:50:38,131 --> 00:50:42,995
♪To truly understand
a love beyond reason♪

723
00:50:42,995 --> 00:50:47,365
♪When I found someone like you♪

724
00:50:47,388 --> 00:50:52,604
♪My whole life no longer
has to keep dreaming♪

725
00:50:52,604 --> 00:50:55,588
♪Now that you're right here♪

726
00:51:03,294 --> 00:51:05,479
Oh wow.

727
00:51:07,265 --> 00:51:10,001
Oh wow.

728
00:51:10,001 --> 00:51:13,127
- All set, thank you.
- Thank you.

729
00:51:14,442 --> 00:51:15,969
Wow.

730
00:51:21,232 --> 00:51:23,124
Well, well.

731
00:51:23,441 --> 00:51:27,541
Seeing this, I'd say you and the Captain
have definitely hooked up.

732
00:51:29,420 --> 00:51:31,687
Are you crazy? Not yet.

733
00:51:32,804 --> 00:51:34,425
The Captain and I just...

734
00:51:35,516 --> 00:51:36,365
kissed.

735
00:51:38,313 --> 00:51:39,476
And how was it?

736
00:51:41,673 --> 00:51:42,812
That's good.

737
00:51:44,140 --> 00:51:47,335
- He made the first move, you know.
- Yeah.

738
00:51:47,335 --> 00:51:50,072
Not gonna lie... this is giving me hope.

739
00:51:50,471 --> 00:51:53,397
But I'm still not really sure
what this thing between us even is.

740
00:51:53,420 --> 00:51:56,122
We're not exactly 'talking,'

741
00:51:56,357 --> 00:51:59,317
but it's not like we're flirting, either.

742
00:51:59,495 --> 00:52:00,950
Mmm.

743
00:52:00,950 --> 00:52:02,325
You've only just started.

744
00:52:02,560 --> 00:52:07,035
Relationships take time.
You've gotta let them develop slowly.

745
00:52:07,987 --> 00:52:10,144
- Yeah, that's true.
- Yeah.

746
00:52:15,035 --> 00:52:16,245
If that's the case,

747
00:52:16,633 --> 00:52:19,229
Right now, I think I won't care.

748
00:52:19,734 --> 00:52:23,258
I'm going to go ahead
and fully court the Captain.

749
00:52:23,258 --> 00:52:24,985
Hey, as for me,

750
00:52:24,985 --> 00:52:27,499
I'm ready to fully support you.

751
00:52:27,499 --> 00:52:29,097
- Oh Tai.
- Haha.

752
00:52:32,504 --> 00:52:33,690
Please go ahead and take your pick.

753
00:52:34,512 --> 00:52:36,426
Hello.

754
00:52:36,509 --> 00:52:38,236
Kenji and Wayu.

755
00:52:41,161 --> 00:52:42,324
Thank you for what's left.

756
00:52:43,805 --> 00:52:45,496
What do you usually like to drink?

757
00:52:45,496 --> 00:52:47,751
- Neat, please.
- Certainly.

758
00:52:51,875 --> 00:52:53,015
Can you finish it in one go?

759
00:52:56,785 --> 00:52:57,620
Another round?

760
00:53:02,330 --> 00:53:04,621
- You're adorable.
- Thank you.

761
00:53:06,583 --> 00:53:08,615
Wayu, go take care of the customers.

762
00:53:09,954 --> 00:53:10,659
Oh.

763
00:53:12,374 --> 00:53:13,244
Sure.

764
00:53:17,108 --> 00:53:21,138
(Customer bought 300 drinks
I'll let you know when I finish work.)

765
00:53:29,009 --> 00:53:29,737
Wayu.

766
00:53:31,828 --> 00:53:32,803
Are you okay, dear?

767
00:53:33,379 --> 00:53:35,058
Hey, were you drugged?

768
00:53:35,329 --> 00:53:37,279
You've been smiling all day.

769
00:53:38,747 --> 00:53:39,405
Eh.

770
00:53:39,769 --> 00:53:42,025
- Eh.
- I'm lovedrunk, Auntie.

771
00:53:42,424 --> 00:53:43,034
Eh.

772
00:53:44,374 --> 00:53:45,948
What's with being lovedrunk?

773
00:53:51,340 --> 00:53:56,027
(Names: Sky, Tai, Richy, Wayu, Kenji,
Edkie, Rudy, Khunthaep, Kaona, Bankbank)

774
00:53:56,862 --> 00:53:57,825
A round of applause.

775
00:54:02,124 --> 00:54:03,652
He'll only stay on top this month.

776
00:54:04,016 --> 00:54:06,306
Next month, he'll drop
to second place anyway.

777
00:54:07,164 --> 00:54:09,619
Excuse me, I should get back
to work now.

778
00:54:12,944 --> 00:54:16,679
♪You are the one that I love♪

779
00:54:18,911 --> 00:54:21,743
Doesn't Wayu seem kinda off?
What got into him?

780
00:54:22,459 --> 00:54:23,070
Huh?

781
00:54:25,290 --> 00:54:26,723
But never mind.

782
00:54:26,935 --> 00:54:31,151
Whatever he's on,
I hope he gets more of it.

783
00:54:31,317 --> 00:54:32,938
That way, sales will keep soaring.

784
00:54:33,490 --> 00:54:35,687
You guys too.

785
00:54:35,992 --> 00:54:37,719
Try boosting your sales for once.

786
00:54:39,322 --> 00:54:40,244
Hmph.

787
00:54:42,650 --> 00:54:43,563
Alas.

788
00:54:45,026 --> 00:54:46,764
Alright, back to work, everyone.

789
00:54:46,776 --> 00:54:48,926
- Yeah.
- Let's go.

790
00:54:50,324 --> 00:54:52,109
- Wayu.
- Yes?

791
00:54:52,109 --> 00:54:54,107
I'm heading out. Can I get a kiss?

792
00:54:54,107 --> 00:54:56,819
Bye-bye.

793
00:54:56,819 --> 00:54:58,371
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

794
00:54:59,863 --> 00:55:01,085
Get home safe.

795
00:55:08,086 --> 00:55:10,248
(MOONLIT)

796
00:55:15,804 --> 00:55:17,531
(Muay Thai)

797
00:55:48,203 --> 00:55:49,261
Do a good job.

798
00:55:49,401 --> 00:55:52,374
This customer reserved you
for 500 drinks.

799
00:56:09,325 --> 00:56:10,159
Excuse me.

800
00:56:15,046 --> 00:56:17,442
I'm Wayu. And you are...?

801
00:56:17,783 --> 00:56:18,382
Pete.

802
00:56:18,958 --> 00:56:20,744
Mr. Pete, are you here alone today?

803
00:56:20,744 --> 00:56:22,259
Then I'll take care of you.

804
00:56:22,611 --> 00:56:24,984
How would you like me
to serve you tonight, Mr. Pete?

805
00:56:24,984 --> 00:56:27,334
As a friend, or more like a boyfriend?

806
00:56:27,334 --> 00:56:29,108
Just let me know, Mr. Pete.

807
00:56:29,953 --> 00:56:31,727
Just sitting and having a drink
together is enough.

808
00:56:36,520 --> 00:56:37,648
You can do that, right?

809
00:56:39,234 --> 00:56:40,738
Of course, I can do that.

